	"__INITIAL_DATA__": {"comments":{"id":27296,"count":327,"talk_id":2678},"threadId":27296,"current_talk":"2678","description":"In 1996, Thordis Elva shared a teenage romance with Tom Stranger, an exchange student from Australia. After a school dance, Tom raped Thordis, after which they parted ways for many years. In this extraordinary talk, Elva and Stranger move through a years-long chronology of shame and silence, and invite us to discuss the omnipresent global issue of sexual violence in a new, honest way. For a Q&A with the speakers, visit go.ted.com/thordisandtom.","event":"TEDWomen 2016","language":"en","name":"Thordis Elva and Tom Stranger: Our story of rape and reconciliation","slug":"thordis_elva_tom_stranger_our_story_of_rape_and_reconciliation","speakers":[{"id":"3054","slug":"thordis_elva","is_published":true,"firstname":"Thordis","lastname":"Elva","middleinitial":"","title":"","description":"Writer","photo_url":"https://pe.tedcdn.com/images/ted/b976b929331c9d44a9d08bebde4ab339ce0ae1f0_254x191.jpg","whatotherssay":"","whotheyare":"Thordis Elva is one of the two authors of \"South of Forgiveness,\" a unique collaboration between a survivor and perpetrator of rape.","whylisten":"<p>Thordis Elva&nbsp;is a firm believer in the healing potential of dialogue when it comes to ending the silence that shrouds sexual violence. In 2015, she was voted Woman of the Year in her native Iceland due to her tireless campaigning for gender equality.</p><p>As&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.thordiselva.com/awards\" target=\"_blank\">an award-winning writer</a>, journalist and public speaker, Elva has utilized many different platforms for her activism, including plays, films and books. Her passion for equality extends to the internet, and she has toured extensively giving lectures about online bullying, non-consensual pornography and digital human rights to audiences such as the United Nations and the Nordic Council of Ministers.</p><p>Read a Q&amp;A with Elva about her TED Talk&nbsp;<a href=\"http://blog.ted.com/a-qa-with-thordis-elva-and-tom-stranger/\" target=\"_blank\">on the TED Blog</a>.&nbsp;</p>"},{"id":"3053","slug":"tom_stranger","is_published":true,"firstname":"Tom","lastname":"Stranger","middleinitial":"","title":"","description":"Co-author, landscape gardener","photo_url":"https://pe.tedcdn.com/images/ted/eb1abc3dbdd2864ac0420823898a07251908f0a4_254x191.jpg","whatotherssay":"","whotheyare":"Tom Stranger is the co-author \"South of Forgiveness.\"","whylisten":"<p>Social sciences and the outdoors have been both professional directions and personal themes for Tom Stranger. After studying social science and working in outdoor recreation, Tom Stranger&#39;s focus shifted towards working with young people with complex needs -- mental health challenges, substance addiction, homelessness and neurological impairment. His time working with young people has taught him the immense value of listening with intent.</p><p>Stranger has recently completed and thoroughly enjoyed a Master of Cultural Studies at the University of Sydney, and he has returned to work in the outdoors as a landscaper. During his studies, he was involved as a co-author in the writing of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.southofforgiveness.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><em>South of Forgiveness</em></a>. He and the book&#39;s primary author, <a href=\"http://www.ted.com/speakers/thordis_elva\" target=\"_blank\">Thordis Elva</a>, share the hope that in speaking up they will add their voices to the ever-growing public discourse around relations of gender and sexual violence.</p><p>Read a Q&amp;A with Stranger about his TED Talk&nbsp;<a href=\"http://blog.ted.com/a-qa-with-thordis-elva-and-tom-stranger/\" target=\"_blank\">on the TED Blog</a>.</p>"}],"url":"https://www.ted.com/talks/thordis_elva_tom_stranger_our_story_of_rape_and_reconciliation","viewed_count":4524756,"talks":[{"recommendations":null,"more_resources":[{"status":"approved","headline":"*South of Forgiveness*","blurb":null,"