>South of Forgiveness</em></a>. He and the book&#39;s primary author, <a href=\"http://www.ted.com/speakers/thordis_elva\" target=\"_blank\">Thordis Elva</a>, share the hope that in speaking up they will add their voices to the ever-growing public discourse around relations of gender and sexual violence.</p><p>Read a Q&amp;A with Stranger about his TED Talk&nbsp;<a href=\"http://blog.ted.com/a-qa-with-thordis-elva-and-tom-stranger/\" target=\"_blank\">on the TED Blog</a>.</p>"}],"speaker_name":"Thordis Elva and Tom Stranger","tags":["activism","collaboration","communication","sexual violence","humanity","identity","personal growth","social change","society","women","men"],"title":"Our story of rape and reconciliation","video_type":{"id":"1","name":"TED Stage Talk"},"viewed_count":4524756}]}
